Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Lamb and Mushroom ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @lamb mince{200%g} to the pan and fry until browned,
~{5-6%mins}. Use #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard
any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince
> is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and stir-fry until golden, ~{3-4%mins}.

== Creamy Sauce ==

Stir the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @dried rosemary{1} into the pan. Cook,
stirring, for ~{1-2%mins}.

Add the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water for the
sauce{100%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened,
~{2-3%mins}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Add a
splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

== Assembly ==

Add the cooked rigatoni to the sauce and stir to combine, then spoon the lamb
ricetta into your #bowls{}. Enjoy!